    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-07-24T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-07-24T06:00:00-05:00" n="414"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d414">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">760N.00/228: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-07-24T14:00:00+03:00"
                            >July 24, 1940—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 24—1:06 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>897. <hi rend="italic">Pravda</hi> today publishes without comment a Tass
                    despatch quoting a Berlin radio communiqué to the effect that Berlin political
                        <pb facs="0415" n="403" xml:id="pg_403"/> circles declare that the entrance
                    of the three Baltic countries into the Soviet Union does not infringe upon
                    Germany’s interests and that Italian political circles state that these events
                    are taking place in a region in which Italy is not interested.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Berlin.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
